## Template 1 — Startup / Scale-Up Product Role

> Use when applying to Series A–C startups, scale-ups, or product-led growth companies

```
[Your name]
[Portfolio URL]  |  [LinkedIn URL]  |  [Email]

[Date]

[Hiring Manager Name or "Design Team at [Company]"]

---

[PARAGRAPH 1 — THE HOOK: something specific about their product]

I've spent the last three months using [Product Name] to [use case], and the
decision to [specific design choice they made — e.g. "surface the activity feed
inline rather than as a separate tab"] is one of the cleaner examples of
prioritising returning users I've seen at this stage of a product.

[PARAGRAPH 2 — THE MATCH: why you + why them]

At [Your Last Company], I owned the redesign of [analogous feature area] for
[similar user type/scale], reducing [metric] by [X]% over [timeframe]. The
challenge of [specific problem they share with your experience] is one I've
navigated before — and I'd bring that approach directly to the [role title] work.

[PARAGRAPH 3 — THE DIFFERENTIATOR: one thing you have that others won't]

Where I'd add something less obvious: I've spent the last two years building
[design system / research infrastructure / 0-to-1 product], which means I can
contribute immediately to [relevant gap or goal from JD] without a long ramp-up.

[PARAGRAPH 4 — THE CLOSE]

I'd welcome a conversation about how I could contribute to [specific product area
or team goal]. A few relevant case studies are at [portfolio URL] — the [Project X]
study maps most closely to the work you're describing.

[First Name Last Name]
```

