## Template 2 — Enterprise / Established Company

> Use when applying to large companies (1000+ employees), agencies, or design-mature orgs

```
[Your name]
[Portfolio URL]  |  [LinkedIn URL]  |  [Email]

[Date]

[Hiring Manager Name]
[Company Name]

---

[PARAGRAPH 1 — ACKNOWLEDGE THEIR SCALE/CONTEXT]

[Company Name]'s approach to [design challenge — e.g. "accessibility across a
multi-product platform" or "design system governance at scale"] is something I've
followed closely — particularly [specific public initiative, blog post, or design
decision you genuinely admire].

[PARAGRAPH 2 — SPECIFIC RELEVANT EXPERIENCE]

In my [X years] working on [analogous domain], I've learned that [insight relevant
to their context]. At [Company], I [specific achievement with metric]. The
[relevant skill from JD] piece is where I've spent the most time, and where I'm
most prepared to contribute from day one.

[PARAGRAPH 3 — YOUR WORKING STYLE AT THIS SCALE]

I work well in complex cross-functional environments — at [previous company] I
collaborated across [N] teams and [Y stakeholders] to ship [outcome]. I understand
that design at [Company's] scale is as much about influence and alignment as it is
about craft, and I've built that muscle deliberately.

[PARAGRAPH 4 — CLOSE]

I'd welcome the chance to discuss the [specific role] in more detail. My portfolio
at [URL] includes [Project Name], which reflects the type of systems-level thinking
the role seems to call for.

[First Name Last Name]
```

