## Template 3 — Career Change / Domain Shift

> Use when the designer is moving from agency to in-house, from one industry to another,
> or from a different creative field into product design

```
[PARAGRAPH 1 — ACKNOWLEDGE THE SHIFT DIRECTLY, DON'T HIDE IT]

I'm making a deliberate move from [previous context — e.g. "agency work for FMCG
brands"] to [new context — e.g. "in-house product design for fintech"], and
[Company Name] is the company I'd most want to do that with.

[PARAGRAPH 2 — BRIDGE YOUR TRANSFERABLE SKILLS]

What I bring from [previous context] that transfers directly: [specific skill 1 —
e.g. "working under rapid timelines with multiple stakeholders"] and [specific
skill 2 — e.g. "visual system design from scratch"]. What I've been building
specifically for this transition: [portfolio project, self-study, course, or
side project in the new domain].

[PARAGRAPH 3 — SHOW YOU UNDERSTAND THEIR WORLD]

I've spent the past [X months] studying [their domain] — including [concrete
research, product usage, reading list]. The [specific insight about their product
challenge or user] shows me this isn't a field I'm guessing about.

[PARAGRAPH 4 — CLOSE WITH CONFIDENCE]

I'm not pitching this as a risk for you — I'm pitching it as someone who brings
[specific unique angle] alongside a genuine desire to go deep in [domain]. I'd
welcome a conversation. Portfolio: [URL].

[First Name Last Name]
```

