## Template 4 — Dream Company / Cold Outreach

> Use when reaching out to a company not actively advertising a role

```
Subject line: Product Designer — interested in [specific team or product area]

[PARAGRAPH 1 — BE DIRECT ABOUT WHAT YOU'RE DOING]

I'm a [title] with [X years] experience in [domain], and I'm reaching out because
[Company Name] has been on my shortlist for over a year. I noticed you don't have
an open design role at the moment — but I wanted to reach out anyway because [specific
and genuine reason, e.g. "the work your team did on the mobile redesign last year
is some of the best interaction design I've seen in [domain]"].

[PARAGRAPH 2 — MAKE A SPECIFIC PITCH]

If there's a future opening — or if you're building toward one — I'd love to be
considered. My background is in [brief summary]. The work I'm most proud of is
[Project] ([portfolio URL]), which I think speaks directly to the kind of problems
[Company Name] is likely working on.

[PARAGRAPH 3 — ASK FOR A LOW-COMMITMENT NEXT STEP]

Even a 20-minute conversation to learn more about your team's direction would be
valuable to me. Happy to share more case studies or a full CV on request.

[First Name Last Name]
[Portfolio URL]
```

