## Phrases to Avoid

These are CV/letter clichés that signal a generic application:

| ❌ Avoid | ✅ Use instead |
|---|---|
| "I am passionate about design" | Show passion through a specific observation about their product |
| "I am a team player" | "Collaborated with [N] cross-functional partners to ship..." |
| "I have a keen eye for detail" | Let your portfolio prove it |
| "I would love the opportunity to..." | "I'd welcome a conversation about..." |
| "Please find attached my CV" | Just attach it — no need to announce it |
| "I believe I would be a great fit" | Show the fit through specific parallels, not self-assessment |
| "I am excited to..." | Lead with something about them, not about you |

